Packages that use CalendarClient
com.phonegap.calendar.android.adapters All classes into com.phonegap.calendar.android.adapters package are implemented in order to make easier the use of the library, here we can obtain object with all the info supported by model layer and the operations that those objects have to perform, it could be considered like an abstraction layer in a higher level adding some business operations.

static CalendarClient CalendarClientFactory.getInstance(android.content.Context context)
          This method creates an instance of Google CalendarClient if it does not exists, for this aim we need use the account manager and the GoogleAccountUtils methods in order to get the access token and fill the corresponding init values into the new ClientCalendar instance
